-- Hong Kong shares fall along with global markets
-- By Chen Yixin and Shanghai Newsroom
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 04:17AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Oct 8 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's benchmark shares fell 0.7 percent on Wednesday, following overseas markets lower after the International Monetary Fund cut its global economic growth forecast.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended down 159.2 points at 23,263.33. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong also lost 0.7 percent. The IMF on Tuesday cut its global economic growth forecasts for the third time this year, suggesting the environment remains difficult for companies, especially ones with multinational exposure.[ID:nW1N0PZ02N]